==Portuguese==
===Etymology===
Latin '''([[mensis]]) [[Martius]]''', (month) of the Roman god Mars.

===Noun===
'''mar.ço''' ''m''.

#the month of [[March]].

====Usage note====
In Portuguese, names of months are usually not capitalized.

